//Java program to check a given number is Palindrome number or not
//Palindrome number is number in which after reversing that number we will get the same result
import java.util.Scanner;
class Palindrome{  
    public static void main(String args[]){  
     Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
     int r,sum=0;
     System.out.println("Enter the value ");    
     int n=sc.nextInt();//It is the number variable to be checked for palindrome  
     
     int temp=n;    
     while(n>0){    
      r=n%10;  //getting remainder  
      sum=(sum*10)+r;    
      n=n/10;    
     }    
     if(temp==sum)    
      System.out.println("palindrome number ");    
     else    
      System.out.println("not palindrome");    
   }  
   }  

HOW I SOLVED THIS:
 Here I have Used Java while loop to perform the number reversing operation 
 
EXPLANTION FOR TOPIC:
Reversing a number means that the digit at the first position should be swapped with the last digit, and the second digit will be swapped with the second last digit,
and so on till the middle element.

POSSIBLE TEST CASES:
1.To check whether the value is not equal to NULL
2.If reverse of the number is same, then the number is a palindrome number.

INPUT 1 : 121
OUTPUT 1 : palindrome number

INPUT 2 : 251
OUTPUT 2 : not palindrome



